description: Linda Danvers, a.k.a. Supergirl, gets a gig as a substitute art teacher at the local high school, while Kara Zor-El, a.k.a. Supergirl, takes the opportunity to experience life firsthand as a normal Earth teenager. The girls better enjoy the moment, because The Fatalist is coming, and he's out to eliminate Supergirl! Of course, now he has a choice of targets...
name: Many Happy Returns, Part 3: Fatalist Attraction

description: Amid ancient Aztec ruins in Mexico, Supergirl, Mary Marvel and Buzz must fend off the attack of the serpent god Quetzlcoatl, who's been resurrected by the Demon Mother Lilith to help execute her master plan. We also learn there may be another snake in the grass lurking nearby, one Supergirl would never suspect!
name: Spiders And Snakes

description: Deep in the heart of the Amazon rainforest lies the original Garden of Eden, the sacred place that Supergirl is convinced holds the earth angel of fire. Unfortunately, thanks to a long-simmering jealousy of Mary Marvel that prompts her to ignore her traveling companion's warnings of a possible trap, Supergirl may wind up destroying the missing earth angel she's been trying to save!
name: Chaos Rains

description:
This is it! Linda Danvers's quest to find the Earth Angel essence that was Supergirl reaches a startling climaxâ€¦though it may not end exactly as she hoped, especially when one of her traveling companions is killed by the Demon Mother, Lilith! Can Linda re-merge with Supergirl? Should she? Or is there another answer? Prepare for the end of this major storyline, and the beginning of a shocking new direction for Supergirl with issue #75!

Everything is resolved after a titanic battle between good and evil. The earth angel that was part of Supergirl merges with Twilight, who is given a chance of redemption. Mary Marvel is restored to life, Supergirl regains most of her abilities, and the evil ones - Hurmizah, Lilith and the Carnivore - are returned to perdition.
name: A Better Angel

description: Featuring the debut of the new art team of Ed Benes & Alex Lei, and an all-new direction for Supergirl! With her personal journeys ended, no Earth Angels, no Chaos Streams, no demons to fight, Linda Danvers can now claim to be the one and only Supergirl, right? Wrong! When a spacecraft crashes down outside Leesburg, Supergirl races over to the destroyed craft to look for survivors, and finds...Supergirl?!? Linda Danvers becomes immersed in a mystery that will shake her very identity and existence.
name: Many Happy Returns

description:
Linda Danvers, a.k.a. Supergirl, has met Kara Zor-El, a.k.a Supergirl...but is she the real deal? Linda's not sure, so she brings Kara to Metropolis to meet a real Kryptonian. Unfortunately, a lot of strange things in the big city are keeping the Man of Steel preoccupied...though they may tie in to the mystery behind Kara's arrival!

Note: This issue takes place during the events of Superman: The Man of Steel #132, and the "Superman" who makes an appearance is actually just an actor given powers by Mr. Mxyzptlk.
name: Many Happy Returns, Part 2

description: The Fatalist has given Johnny Rebel the means and support to defeat Supergirl...both of them! Meanwhile, it's the first day of school for new student Kara Zor-El and Leesburg High's newest substitute art teacher, Linda Danvers. Looks like detention can be dangerous, and the Girls of Steel are both in for harsh lessons!
name: Many Happy Returns, Part 4: Bad Choices

description: Linda winds up living someone else's life...that of the Silver Age Supergirl! But that's just the beginning of this issue's shocking twists!
name: Many Happy Returns, Part 5: Strange Visitor

description: The final showdown between Supergirl, Kara and Xenon! Will Supergirl manage to prevent Xenon from breaking free? Will Kara catapult herself through time so that her rocketship avoids falling through the time rip in the first place - thus sentencing her to future death? Lives end and begin in this final chapter of Supergirl.
name: Many Happy Returns, Conclusion: Hail & Farewell

description:
If the X-Men want to save Hannah Connover from an alien infection, they must defeat the Queen Brood! But Jean Grey has reservations about this strategy, and the X-Men decide to find another way to infiltrate the Brood.

The X-Men continue their defense of Hannah Connover from the Brood Firstborn assassins onslaught. Hannah is beginning to turn into a Brood Queen, Wolverine wants to kill her but Cyclops convinces him not to. Hannah, suicidal, escapes the X-Men's watch and a battle ensues between the Firstborn assassins and her own Brood offspring. The X-Men arrive too late and Hannah's Brood is killed and Cannonball flies her to safety while the team fights off the Firstborn.

Meanwhile Hannah's husband, Reverend Connover is captured by Firstborns as bait. Hannah sensed this and turns into a full Brood Queen in order to save her husband. After a brief fight, Hannah reverts back to her human self horrified at what she had become. The Reverend tells her she would be forgiven and the Firstborn arrive prepared to finish her.

The X-Men return and theorize that if Iceman froze Hannah, the Brood would believe her dead. Iceman turns Hannah into a popsicle and the remaining Firstborn retreat. The X-Men take Hannah, still in stasis, back to their mansion to find a cure for her, while her husband prays for her and the X-Men. Xavier says he will send her to Muir Isle for treatment.
name: Day of Wrath Part 2

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
In the middle of the extreme battle against quantum, Proctor has created a team of young nu-gene: the New Men.Â 
After a big Basket-ball party, Byrd, Kodiak, Exit, Dash and reign have to fight their first enemy: Elemental.

During the Cold War, Loganâ€”along with Team Xâ€”performed several secret missions inside Russia, one of which was the sabotage of Russiaâ€™s fledgling â€œSuper Soldierâ€ program and the destruction of the programâ€™s result--in particular, the psychotic cyborg known as Omega Red. Loganâ€™s memory of this mission has only recently returned to him...but Omega Red has thought of nothing else ever since. Itâ€™s time for some payback.
name: Savior, Pt. 2

description: While Omega Red holds Jubilee hostage and with S.H.I.E.L.D. hot on his trail, Logan makes his way to Berlin - the site of an ill-fated mission during his time in Team X - to retrieve an ellusive artifact from the Cold War: the carbonadium synthesizer. Omega Red wants the synthesizer so that he can stabilize the deadly carbonadium bonded to his body-but can he be trusted to deliver on his end of the bargain? Of course not. Logan has a plan, though-but he's going to need some help from an old friend to pull it off.
name: Savior, Pt. 3

description: The Chain Gang may be just what the people want, but the cops are none too pleased with this vigilante crew. That doesn't stop the trio from hunting druglord 8-Ball in his den of vice...especially when the neighborhood sides with reporter Marion Hawley against the police in support of the Chain Gang!
name: The House of Corrections

description: It's heavy-metal action as Zecker and Animal settle their differences...with a chainsaw! But the Chain Gang's mission may be in jeopardy when Sergeant Shanahan gets a lead on their identity and Deathstroke the Terminator is hired to take them down!
name: Weak Link

description: Special guest star Deathstroke the Terminator joins the hunt for the Chain Gang. And in a series where no one is safe, the Animal confronts Curtis with a chainsaw!
name: Cold Cuts

description: Both the new Batman (Azrael) and Deathstroke the Terminator make guest appearances in this issue. The Chain Gang struggles with its violent past as Deathstroke the Terminator lays siege to the Chain Gang's House of Correction...and the new Batman, disgusted with what passes for justice in Gotham City, pays a call.
name: Reunion

description: Featuring an appearance by the new Batman (Azrael). Deathstroke the Terminator proves hard to defeat...but not too hard for the Chain Gang! Plus, Yale finally loses his cool and hunts for the murderous and well-connected Shavers.
The Chain Gang pays an explosive visit to a private prison owned by 'The Crooked Man,' an underworld kingpin whose mind is as twisted as his body.
name: Jailbreak

description: The Chain Gang makes explosive surgical strikes on a number of illegal gambling dens owned by 'The Crooked Man,' a twisted criminal mastermind with the entire city in his clutches...and a sick combat arena in his mansion called 'The Pit.'
name: Are Ya Ready To Rumble

description: It's rampant destruction as the Chain Gang sets out to stop 'The Crooked Man,' whose latest multibillion-dollar scheme jeopardizes innocent lives when a property is earmarked for demolition.
name: The Nightshift

description: While Batman (Azrael) speeds toward the Crooked Man's mansion, the Chain Gang storms the premises in an all-out attack. Meanwhile, Deathstroke the Terminator escapes the House of Correction.
name: The Welcome to the Pit

description: The new Batman (Azrael) guest-stars as he joins the Chain Gang's battle with the Crooked Man. Meanwhile, carnage ensues at the House of Correction as Curtis imposes his brutal sentence.
name: Knightshift

description: Pete Wisdom has a lot of fairies to kill. Yes, fairies are supposed to be nice and magical and charming, but they are currently attacking England.
name: The Rudiments of Wisdom Part 1: The Day the Fairies Came Out

description: The new Captain Comet and his "friend" Tyrone keep it real on Hardcore Station, and the Weird gets even Weirder!
name: Weird and Weirder

description: Final issue. Batman (Azrael) appears as the Chain Gang's explosive confrontation with the Crooked Man leads to the revelation of the final fate of the Gang and its underworld prisoners.
name: Meltdown

description: Body-snatchers on Hardcore Station! Intergalactic intrigue! Murderers at large! Mystery in Space!
name: Question of Resurrection

description: Face-to-face with his mysterious foes, Captain Comet is not going to like what he sees! And The Weird finds religion??
name: Going Dark

description: IN THE BELLY OF THE BEAST! The Mystery goes undercover when Comet imfiltrates the Eternal Light Corporation!
name: Holy Warriors

description: Comet wrestles in the jaws of death when the league of Insect Assassins makes him a marked man!
name: BUGS!

description:
Overview

Continued from Punisher War Journal #61 and Punisher War Zone #23. After mobsters decide to end their Punisher problem, Frank destroys their Manhattan tower and apparently dies along with them. This brings the unwanted attention of the FBI and V.I.G.I.L. However, Punisher is not dead, and he struggles to remove himself from the rubble.

Story continues in Punisher War Journal #62.
name: Suicide Run, part 3: Deadline

description: Hot artist Ben Oliver (Vigilante) joins the terrific Robert Kirkman for a new 3-issue arc! The mysterious mutant called Magician is plunged into the world of the X-Men, adjusting quickly and making new friends fast. But there is something deeply sinister about the newcomer. Something only young Kitty Pryde notices. Letâ€™s hope she hasnâ€™t noticed too late. Meanwhile, is Jean Grey really the cosmic entity called Phoenix? And if so...what can be done about it...?
name: Phoenix?: Part 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The counter-culture private detective of the 1960s is brought to the '90s with a Vertigo twist. Jonny Double follows a heist gone wrong and its deadly consequences. When Jonny agrees to keep tabs on a rich man's wayward twentysomething daughter Faith, he becomes ensnared in a tangled web of deceit, murder and double-cross that pits his '60s idealism against '90s cynicism. When Jonny helps Faith and her friends with a get-rich-quick scheme involving a long-forgotten bank account belonging to Al Capone, they soon discover that the account wasn't closed after all...and that they've taken the money from someone very alive, very dangerous and very hot on their trail.
name: Two-Finger Discount Pt. 1

description:
Overview

Continued from Punisher War Zone #24.

There is an army of Punishers running amok. Pierce, Outlaw, Lynn Michaels, and Swaybrick all seemingly take turns as the Punisher. Some are out for justice while others are out for themselves, each vying for the attention of the public and criminals alike.

Continued in Punisher War Journal #63
name: Suicide Run Part 6: False Moves

description:
"Suicide Run, Part 9 - Past the Point of Rescue"

Continued from Punisher War Zone #25.

The Sheriff of Laastekist releases the Punisher as his town descends into chaos. Frank Castle unleashes against the invaders. The various versions of Punisher also converge on Laastekist, making the town even more volatile.

Concluded in Punisher War Journal #64.
name: Suicide Run Part 9: Past The Point Of Rescue

description: We follow Nick Fury as he inner Monologues to us all of the things we are actually seeing him do, and his motivations for doing them. At the same time someone has hired an assassin to take him out. Nick knows who the assassin is and respects his skill enough to try and stop him .
name: The Reserves

description:
Overview

The ULTIMATES return in this BLOCKBUSTER first issue! It's been one year since they stopped an alien invasion, and now things get hard. New members, new costumes and 12 months of gossip to catch up on! Who's getting married? Who's divorced? Who's gone nuts since we last saw them?
name: Gods & Monsters

description:
North Atlantic, 1945:

America launches it's attack on Germany, and try to stop their secret weapon from being released on the United States. Still, the Americans have their own secret weapon, one that stands for all the hearts of the soldiers giving their lives. Captain America.

Iceland, 06:00 hours:

The raid against the world's major evil begins as American soldiers dive from the air, jumping into combat. Hell has come to Earth as guns are fired, bombs explode, and many good men have lost their lives. All would seem lost if it wasn't for the fact that a large transporter driven by Cap diving from the sky crashing into the enemy's base, killing many Nazis and opening a hole in the impenetrable wall. After all Cap say's parachutes are for girls.

In the war zone Cap stands tall against the Nazi threat, and he single handedly lead his forces into the enemy base. As the Nazi's secret weapon launches for Washington D.C., all seems lost. Only one man however can stop the weapon. In a split second Cap grabs onto the missile, rips open a panel to the guidance system and takes a grenade from his belt and tosses in in the Nazi missile. In an instant, an explosion lights the skies of Iceland. Captain America had been confirmed to have died in the explosion.

His fiance back home Gail Richards is given Cap's last letter. Cap....Steve tells his love he is sorry and goodbye. For many years afterward all believe Cap to be dead, but this hero will eventually rise from their grave.

Mount Everest, 2002:

As a young Tony Stark gazes into the mountain ranges, he sees hope and encouragement in Stark International. He waxes philosophic to Happy Hogan and shows he knows more about the company than some might think. He then sets up a meeting in Manhattan, New York...9:15 sharp.
name: Super Human

description: Jonny and his gang raid the long-forgotten bank account belonging to Al Capone, only to discover that the account wasn't closed after all! The scene smells of a set-up, but a few things are certain: they've taken someone's money, he's hot on their trail, and that someone just might be closer than they think.
name: Two-Finger Discount Pt. 2

description: On the lam with Al Capone's money, Jonny's gang is being picked off by a brutal and mysterious killer who keeps his victims' hands as trophies. But who is he? Has the gang been set up? And could Al Capone actually still be alive?
name: Two-Finger Discount Pt. 3

description: Who killed Detective Brannigan? Where the hell is Faith? And exactly whose money did Jonny and his gang steal? All secrets are revealed when Jonny faces off with the mysterious hitman known as Mr. Shiver.
name: Two-Finger Discount Pt. 4

description:
Ash takes on Federal Agents with fake guns and meets Gabriel.

Pin up by Geof Darrow.
name: Ghost and the Machine

description:
Ash meets Gabriel and The Actor.

Pin up by Jim Lee.
name: Ashes to Ashes

description: People in Wiltshire are having nightmares. This wouldn't be a problem if there weren't soldiers from the nearby military base shooting the place up because of their bad dreams. It's up to Pete Wisdom and MI 13 to get to the bottom of it. Little do they know that this threat threatens all of Great Britain and the whole world!
name: The Rudiments of Wisdom Part 2: The Village that walked like a Woman

description: Thereâ€™s a dragon running the Welsh mob. And thatâ€™s not a metaphor. A fire-breathing, giant lizard is running the mob and the Welsh police canâ€™t handle it. This falls under the purview of Pete Wisdom and MI 13. And theyâ€™re calling in some extra help to handle this problem as SHANG-CHI, MASTER OF KUNG FU shows up in this issue!
name: The Rudiments of Wisdom Part 3: Enter With Drag On

description: Pete Wisdom is up to his neck in Jack the Rippers-- every version of him that anyone's ever thought of. All this due to a man who can access alternate universes. At a time like this, Wisdom wouldn't want British Intelligence to turn against him, would he?
name: The Rudiments of Wisdom Part 4: Too Many Jacks

description:
Is there hope for Pennystown?

Don't miss the final issues of GIRLS, which concludes at issue #24!

The Punisher is sentenced to death for killing Nick Fury. Frank Castle is electrocuted and believed dead once and for all. However, the Punisher survived since his death was staged by the mob. The boss of the mob family doesn't want the Punisher dead...he wants him to take over his crime family!
name: Condemned

description:
As dusk descends over the Ashford tournament, Dunk and his runaway squire, Egg, recover from the horror they just witnessed and prepare for Dunk's upcoming combat in the tournament. But Dunk's first combat takes an unexpected, and potentially deadly, form when he chooses to defend a helpless puppeteer, Tanselle (a girl Dunk has more than a passing interest in) from the brutal hand of Aerion, a prince of the blood of the dragon. When the dust settles, lies are revealed, lives are destroyed, true natures are exposed, and Dunk finds himself with an opponent he cannot hope to defeat, the law of the realm!

SPOILERS

Ser Arlan of Pennytree, a hedge knight decades past his prime, is dead. Dunk, his squire, buries him and pays his last respects. After some thought, Dunk decides to continue to Ashford and compete in the tourney as a knight, a title to which he has no claim.

Nevertheless, he takes Ser Arlan's armor, money and three horses, and travels on to an inn down the road. Here he meets up with a young orphan boy named Egg. Egg begs Dunk to take him to the tourney with him, but Dunk refuses, so Egg secretly follows him to Ashford.
name: Chapter 4

volume.name: George R.R. Martin's The Hedge Knight

description:
Fei Long is attacked by the yakuza after refusing to bow to their whims, and Cammy's investigation into her origins becomes more mysterious than ever.

MAIN STORY:

We open on Killer Bee murdering her way past several enemy agents. She shuts her eyes for a moment and suddenly she is back, floating in a tank at Shadaloo, with a monsterous, fanged version of M. Bison watching her. A putton is pushed and the tank starts to empty... and Cammy wakes up, sitting upright in her bed.

Cammy immediately calls Colonel Wolfman and tells him that this is the first dream she has ever had, and something about it felt familiar, somehow tied to her past. She says she had the same feeling from the girl they captured last issue. Wolfman says for her to get some sleep, and that MI-6 will get any info they can use out of the girl the next day. Cammy signs off, looking at her facial scar.

Meanwhile at Hong Kong Police Headquarters, Chun-Li is being told by her superior that she has shut down more Shadaloo cells in Hong Kong then the rest of the agents combined, and that is why he is trusting her with this next assignment. He says that Shadaloo has managed to infiltrate the Hong Kong film industry, and that one agent has lost his life looking into this. Before he did, he told the paramedic trying to save him, "Get to Fei Long."

Elsewhere in Hong Kong, Fei Long faces the group of thugs from last issue. They tell him that he was unwise to turn down Ladies Xiayu and Yanyu's offer of a starring role in thier next project. The thugs attack, and Fei Long beats them all. The last one scurries away, telling Fei Long that Xiayu and Yanyu will make him sorry.

At MI-6 Headquarters in London, Cammy examines the Shadaloo prisoners items. Picking up Juli's arm gauntlets, she says that they seem familiar, then asks to see the prisoner.

The agent helping Cammy tells her that they have gotten nothing from her thus far. He says it took a dozen men to subdue her, and she has been quiet since.

As soon as Cammy is left alone in Juli's presence, Juli salutes her. "Agent Satsuki, reporting, Agent Killer Bee!"

Playing along, Cammy discovers that Juli believes her to be her superior, and that her capture in Germany was in order to not blow "Killer Bee's" cover. Juli tells Cammy that Commander Bison took considerable damage in Japan, but thanks to the technology that Cammy procured for an experimental weapon, he is recuperating. She also says the power levels on the weapon itself have already exceeded projections, and will soon surpass the capabilities of every nuclear power in the world. Cammy asks if it is complete, and Juli responds "nearly." Juli tells her that after she assassinated the team of scientists working on the weapon, Shadaloo has worked tirelessly on creating a prototype. The revelation she is responsible for so many murders leaves Cammy shaken.

In Japan, Kei receives a letter from Sakura. Sakura says she is having a blast, training with Ryu in Thailand, then asks her to mail some letters to her parents. It seems that since she knew they would never let her go off and train with Ryu, she told them she was stayin with Kei and Kei's parents in Tobu. Kei is less than pleased to be part of her deception.

Meanwhile, in Thailand, Ryu and Sakura are confronted by Adon. "We meet at last!" He says.

BACK UP STORY

Sakura hurries to school on her bike, when she is suddenly cut off by a limo. Out steps Karin Kanzuki, who tells Sakura they had a rematch scheduled. "AFTER my exams!" Sakura protests, but Karin says she's just stalling because she knows her earlier victory was a fluke, and comes at her. The two of them fight, but once Sakura realizes she's late for class she runs off, leaving behind a furious Karin.
name: Stage 08

description: Adon attacks! To defend the honour of Muay Thai, Adon tracks down Ryu for the ultimate martial arts showdown. Plus, Fei-Long meets his toughest challenge yet, and her name is Chun-Li!
name: Stage 09

description: Would you like to see Fei Long, Chun-Li, and Gen fight hundreds of ninjas? Trust us, YOU WOULD!
name: Stage 10

description: The rematch of the century! Chun-Li and Cammy return for Round Two, in an incredibly epic battle! Plus, a secret from Ryu's past surfaces!
name: Stage 11

description:
KEN and ELIZA had hoped that their wedding preparations would run smoothly, but those plans come to an abrupt halt when VEGA crashes their wedding shower with one thing on his mind: revenge. However, this fight is one Ken fortunately won't need to fight alone. Meanwhile in Brazil, CAMMY and CHUN-LI try to get to the bottom of Shadaloo's secret weapons programs, but discover something even more disturbing: BISON HAS RETURNED!

PLUS! Acclaimed artist ADRIAN (RUNAWAYS) ALPHONA provides a cover and backup story featuring one of CAMMY,s and DELTA RED's earliest missions!

Note: The regular cover was done by Alvin Lee, the "Special Power Foil Cover" was done by Jo Chen.
name: Stage 12

description:
The Street Fighters head to Vegas! In this pen-ultimate issue of Street Fighter, the World Warriors rest for the epic battle ahead. Ken hits the tables, Ryu and Sakura hit the buffet, and Vega and Bison crash the wedding!

Backup story: Zangief vs. R. Mika.
name: Stage 13

description: The epic conclusion to Street Fighter! This marriage will be one for the books, as the reception ends in the greatest martial arts battle of all time! From this fight relationships will end, friendships will be forged, and the World Warriors will prepare for their next epic battle... in STREET FIGHTER II!
name: Stage 14

description: Magicianâ€™s trial by fire into the world of the X-Men is kicked up a notch when he and Cyclops find themselves face to face with a thousand pounds of immovability called The Blobâ€”and his bouncing buddy the terrible Toad! Will the fledgling X-Man have what it takes? Meanwhile, the quest to learn what is really happening with Jean Grey takes a totally unexpected turn. You have been warned.
name: Phoenix?: Part 2

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The quest to learn if Jean Grey is, in fact, the Phoenix reaches a shattering conclusion! And the mystery surrounding the X-Men's newest member, the Magician, deepens-as Nick Fury starts putting the pieces together!
name: Phoenix?: Part 3

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Â 
In the streets of No Man's Land, Batman, Robin, and the Penguin fight to save Two-Face in the conclusion to "Goin" Downtown!" While Two-Face faces the wrath of various gangs, Bane's plan to destroy the future of Gotham City is realized in a shocking climax! Â  Â 
Â 
Story continued from: Batman #571

Gotham City has been devastated by a terrible earthquake. Gotham lies in ruins and has been declared a disaster area by the U.S. government. Two-Face has been running things from City Hall. Bane takes out Two-Faceâ€™s guys at City Hall, and Two Face is captured and held on mock trial by the rest of Gotham gangers. They decide to hang him. Meanwhile the Penguin keeps track of what is happening from a distance. Batman and Robin are forced to save Two-Face from the Gangers. The comic ends with Bane blowing up City Hall and all the cityâ€™s records.

Oracle, Harvey Bullock and Batgirl make cameo appearances, they react to the explosion.

This comic is part of the No Manâ€™s Land story line
name: Goin Downtown (Part 2): The Vandal

description:
Not in this issue: The Nextwave squad runs a marathon! Who wins? Who loses? Who crawls over the finish line? Also, they drink lots of Bromo-Fizz!

In this issue: Oh, no! The Mindless Ones are loose in an American Town and only Nextwave can stop them! Watch people get kicked and things explode!

Isnâ€™t what happens more exciting than what doesnâ€™t happen? LIFE IS GREAT!

The Nextwave Squad travels to the town of Shotcreek to investigate and prevent the Beyond Corporation from completing the "Magic Deal" listed in their marketing plan.

The marketing plan is a document that Beyond is using to organize the testing of their UWMD (Unusual Weapons of Mass Destruction). The "magic deal" involves contact with the Dread Rorkannu or the Dank Dimension. Beyond Corp wants to rent the Mindless Ones. Dread Rorkannu demands payment in girls. Cash also works. Dread Rorkannu prefers the suicide girls, with tattoos and piercings...no blondes.

Meanwhile on the Shockwave Rider, The Captain explains to Aaron Stack why he is simply The Captain. He tried other names but they never worked out like Captain Power, Captain Ron, Captain L. Ron, Captain Universe, Captain Ultra, Captain Avenger, Captain Avalon, Captain Marvel and even Captain Kerosene. Elsa and Photon are having their own discussions, Photon admits that the worst part of being on the Avengers was that she was hit on by almost all of them...except Captain America.

Shotcreek is quickly overrun by destructive mindless ones. By the time Newtwave arrives there are over 200 mindless ones terrorizing the city. They are able to beat the first section of mindless ones and begin to spread out to the north.

Max's plans enter their final, fatal stage in Part 2 of the 3-part "Anti-Heist." 300 pounds of weapons-grade plutonium will fall into the wrong hands if the Losers can't convince a transport ship that they're not the enemy. But it may already be too late, because there's a submarine on the horizon aiming to kill, one helmed by an adversary who knows the Losers' tricks all too well...
name: The Anti-Heist, Part Two

description: The very ship the Losers came out to help is sinking. Its crew is drowning. Max's reinforcements have arrived. Their ally-turned-adversary, Roque, has gotten his hands on 300 pounds of weapons-grade plutonium, and his men have the upper hand. Now it's up to the Losers to go on the offensive and take it all away from them...
name: The Anti-Heist, Conclusion

description: Legendary artist Colin Wilson (Lt. Blueberry, POINT BLANK) visits the Losers in Part 1 of the thrilling new 3-part story arc "Unamerica." Max's mysterious "Project" is revealed as a massive seismic event rocks the Persian Gulf. But his plans also hinge on another key element: an arsenal of nuclear warheads hidden in a ghost town near Chernobyl. And with the background radiation masking the warhead emissions, the Losers might as well be looking for a needle in a stack of needles...
name: UnAmerica, Part One

description: Featuring art by the acclaimed Colin Wilson (Lt. Blueberry). His master plan accomplished, Max is now an international threat. But before the Losers can get to him, one of their own is captured in a scenario they may be unable to think their way out of.
name: UnAmerica, Part Two

description: Concluding a 3-part arc with art by Colin Wilson (Lt. Blueberry). It's Roque vs. the Losers, and the stakes are the fate of Max's nuclear arsenal, an entire nation under his control and the life of Pooch,who stands on the brink of execution. The Losers are out of time, out of ideas and out of luck...
name: UnAmerica, Conclusion

description: Part 1 of 'Endgame.' It's all been building to this: With New Jerusalem behind him, Max lays it all on the line - his plans, his origins, and the stakes, which are nothing short of global. Now it's Max vs. the Losers with the world hanging in the balance, and the Losers will have to play every card in their hand to win.
name: Endgame, Part One

description: 'Endgame' continues as the Losers take the fight to Max's door. Now, after all these years, the Losers are getting their payback against the man who destroyed their lives, but none of them are prepared for Max's greatest secret. Their surprise will cost them dearly...
name: Endgame, Part Two

description: 'Endgame' continues. As the Losers reel from the devastating toll suffered last issue, Max's origin and his ties to the CIA are finally revealed. But just as the team and Max are playing with all their cards on the table, one final twist awaits to threaten them all.
name: Endgame, Part Three

description: Clay. Aisha. Cougar. Pooch. Jensen. Max. It's their final battle as the Eisner-nominated series ends with a bang, bloodshed, and a whole lot of bodies...but how many of them belong to the Losers? Final issue.
name: Endgame, Conclusion

description: Writer Devin Grayson (NIGHTWING) is joined by illustrator extraordinaire Brian Stelfreeze (BATMAN: LEGENDS OF THE DARK KNIGHT) for an explosive miniseries pitting Lt. Isabel Cardona against a deadly serial killer! Dismissed as a quota minority hire by her work peers, Cuban-born and Florida-bred Detective Isabel Cardona makes no friends on the Miami force by insisting that a series of seemingly unrelated murder cases lead to an urban-legend killer known only as "The Matador." Proving his existence soon becomes her only way to prove her sanity, but how close to the dangerous Matador will Cardona have to get to make that happen? Â
name: Sym-me-try

person_credits.name: Brian Stelfreeze
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover

description: The Punisher has done something no one could have seen coming...he willingly became head of a crime family! Frank Castle is now the don of the Geraci crime family and the members are not pleased with this. Most of the family wants to kill Castle so Frank has to punish them to keep the in line. Castle can't kill them or he risks losing control of the crime family so the Punisher has to do something he almost never does...The Punisher has to punish criminals without killing them!
name: Family

description: The Geraci crime family's turf is being attacked by the Yakuza and the Punisher is forced to defend his crime family's turf! The Punisher kills several Yakuza gang members and ends up forcing the leaders to bring in a meta human Hachiman to kill the Punisher and save face for the Yakuza.
name: Hatchet Job

description: Daredevil beats up some mobsters in Hell's Kitchen asking them who do they work for. When they say "Frank Castle" Daredevil doesn't believe them. When he tracks them down to their headquarters and finds out they were telling the truth he doesn't know what to think. Meanwhile the Punisher is finding life in the mob to be a bit more complicated then he thought. Things get even more complicated for Castle when he finds out Jigsaw is killing people dressed up as the Punisher.
name: Clash

description: The crime families of New York City have gathered to discuss business. None of them are happy about the Punisher becoming the head of the Geraci crime family. Rosalie Carbone won't let her hatred of Frank Castle die and has her family launch an attack on The Punisher and the rest of the crime families to kill Frank once and for all. The Punisher and Rosalie have their final showdown which only one of them will survive.
name: Firepower!

description: The Russian mob under Firefox is trying to muscle in on the Geraci crime family. The Punisher will protect his crime syndicate at all costs and shows the Russians why they should have just stayed home.
name: Hostage To The Devil

description: Mikel Fury is mad as hell after finding out the Punisher is alive. Mikel sets out to kill the Punisher using all available SHIELD resources. The Punisher is not willing to let Mikel just kill him and ambushes his strike unit. The Geraci Family not wanting to see their leader getting murdered by SHIELD attacks them leading to organized crime vs SHIELD battle.
name: He's Alive?!

description: Move over Punisher! A new vigilante is town! After the death of his family, the vigilante Mortalis goes gunning after a senator under Punisher's protection. Frank must fight back sympathies for the killer in order to protect the Geraci family.
name: Vengeance Is Mine!

description: Frank grapples with his torn loyalties as he juggles his role as leader of the Geraci family, budding feelings for Leslie Geraci, and his desire to return to his war on crime. Add as slew of villains including Jigsaw and Tombstone to that, and Frank must deal with a potent mixture of betrayal and violence.
name: Tumbling Down

description: Jigsaw and Punisher face off! When Jigsaw invades the Geraci complex, Punisher returns to his war on crime to stop the threat his old nemesis poses. Returning to the war comes with a price, though. Will Punisher decide people cannot change or will he be able to save what is left of the Geraci family?
name: Last Shot Fired

description:
"Police Action, Part 2 of 3"

V.I.G.I.L. and Punisher are spiraling towards a head-on collision when Punisher target the same criminal. Despite Microchip's warning, Punisher continues with the mission. But can Punisher finish the job before VIGIL crashes the party?
name: Police Action: Part 2

description: Punisher has survived fighting common thugs, drug lords, and super-villains, but can he beat the Reavers? A computer hacking mistake on Micro's part leads the Reavers right to Frank Castle's doorstep. Is Punisher ready to roll out the welcome mat or is this it for the skull-chested vigilante?
name: Reaver Fever

description: While staking out a cocaine warehouse, Punisher discovers the operation is being run by none other than his long-time nemesis Jigsaw. Punisher destroys the warehouse, but jigsaw survives the blast and manages to escape. Upon returning to his own safehouse, Punisher and Micro have a falling out over Micro's lack of involvement and interest in Punisher's war on crime. Jigsaw turns to the Rev for assistance, who has now become a Satan worshiper due to his disillusionment caused by his encounters with Punisher. Upon further analysis, the drug found in the warehouse was not cocaine, but rather it was a highly concentrated poison. The Punisher decides to investigate further.
name: Jigsaw Puzzle: Part 1

description: Travel to a time of sword and sorcery; a time of dragons and damsels in distress! Welcome to the world of Dragon's Lair! Follow Dirk the Daring and Princess Daphne as they return from an astonishing adventure in the Free Realms only to be attacked by the great dragon, Singe, and his evil minions. Singe vows revenge against Dirk for killing his offspring, and Daphne is soon caught in the dreaded dragon's claws. Now, armed with his courage and skill, Dirk must brave the Dark Kingdom and all its evils in order to save the Princess from Singe!
